lead_paragraph: The New Orleans Bulletin says that the band of men who had organized at that city, for the invasion of Cuba, has been disbanded, and that fifteen hundred or two thousand young and adventurous spirits, who had come together from ever section of the union with highest hopes, thus go home disappointed and impoverished.
